cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper involves the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) to generate images, specifically oil paintings. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of various GAN architectures, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also evaluates the generated images quantitatively using a distance metric, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
